title: India to launch 104 satellites in single space mission
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device India to launch 104 satellites in single space mission 14 February 2017 Last updated at 06:49 GMT 
India is set to launch a record 104 satellites into space in a single mission on 15 February. 
Although there is no direct space rivalry between China and India some analysts have compared it to the US-Soviet "space race".
